      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine. This M96 powerplant delivers 320 hp through a G96 6-speed manual transaxle with precise shift linkage and a healthy clutch take-up. The chassis remains taut, utilizing a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension geometry that provides exceptional communicative feedback through the hydraulic steering rack. Braking is handled by four-piston aluminum monobloc calipers paired with vented, cross-drilled rotors for superior heat dissipation. Crucially, the IMS bearing has been addressed with a dual-row ceramic retrofit, and the rear main seal (RMS) remains dry, indicating excellent crankcase integrity. The cooling system has been refreshed with a high-flow water pump to mitigate thermal load. This is a high-performance, driver-spec 911 optimized for longitudinal and lateral acceleration.",
